# Project Rules

- This repository is the source of truth for the Hammerspoon setup.
- Keep source code in `/Users/diaoyuxuan/hammerspoon-config`.
- Do not write new feature logic into `~/.hammerspoon/init.lua`; that file is only a bootstrap.
- Keep runtime state such as TODO data outside Git.
- Prefer small, focused modules under `modules/`.
- Update docs when behavior, module boundaries, hotkeys, or architecture change.
- When adding a standalone feature, prefer a new module plus a toggle in `modules/modules_enabled.lua`.
- Keep paths and constants centralized in `modules/config.lua`.

# Working Style

- Make changes that are easy for a solo developer to understand later.
- Optimize for maintainability and low surprise.
- Preserve the existing macOS/iOS-style launcher direction unless explicitly asked to redesign it.
